INSERT INTO `movies` VALUES (1,'Eternals','For several thousand years, aliens have inhabited the blue planet. Arrived on Earth, representatives of the most ancient race, referred to as the Eternals, they perform a difficult mission. Their task is to protect earthlings from the monstrous creatures of the Deviants. The latter are the most dangerous creatures from galactic space, who have been opposed by alien warriors for years. Today they have a different task - to control and monitor people\'s lives without interfering in the development process. Well, maybe just a little, stimulating the techno boom. Actions acquire dynamics in the present time, on the verge of the inevitable. The earth must wake up. And this threatens with irreversible consequences - destruction. The main characters in an accelerated mode need to prevent the death of the planet they are in love with, the people they are attached to.',185),(2,'The Cloverfield Paradox','The population of the planet is once again exposed to serious danger. The impractical consumption of natural resources is about to lead to their natural depletion, which will entail the inevitable death of life on Earth. In order to prevent an energy collapse, a group of brave astronauts is sent to the bowels of the galactic space for experimental experiments. In order to achieve an alternative supply of mankind with the sources of necessary energy, scientists are conducting a number of studies. And, while there are debates on the planet between the leaders of states, while civilization is on the verge of extinction, researchers are trying to do the impossible. At the Cloverfield orbital station, they are tasked with troubleshooting the rotation of the particle accelerator, which will be the key to the operation of the infinite energy derivative. Several attempts to start the device do not bring results, which causes tension in the team. When the unit begins to gain power, a monstrous, irreparable mistake occurs.',96),(3,'The Titan','When the scale of depleted natural resources exceeds all acceptable limits, a secret government organization offers an alternative solution to the inevitable disappearance of civilization. The best minds of scientists begin to work on a project to create a superman, who will be able to withstand natural disasters and force majeure circumstances of a concentrated nature. Developed through innovative technologies based on crossbreeding, such a person will become the mainstay of a new race. A colony of people of the future will be resettled on the planet Titan, where they will continue their rescue mission to continue the human race. The pioneers of such an unpredictable experiment are a group of strong and stern men who have dedicated their lives to serving the good of their homeland. The test takes place during the year and brings positive results. Researchers are ready to bring nanotechnology to the masses...when the side effects start showing up.',65),(4,'The Congress','The future of the world is hazy and blurry. This is due to the rapid development of innovative technologies. For this reason, the boundaries of real and virtual reality are blurred. There are fears that soon no one will be able to distinguish reality from fiction. Robin Wright has been a sought-after actress in the past. But all the best roles that she could have played on stage have already been played. Now she has to be content with little, not sorting out with offers. When a major film studio offers to scan her image to use later without her permission in any filming, Robin does not have to interfere and she agrees. Her son Aaron needs medical attention, so the actress does not think for a long time. Since then, more than a dozen years have passed. Robin arrives by invitation to a convention held in a fictional world. Now the future is in her hands - to stay in the past, where there are no jobs, no prospects, but there is a son who needs help. Or choose a bright future, where she is destined for the role of a screen star.',45),(5,'Deck the Halls','Steve Finch is used to an orderly lifestyle. As befits a perfectionist, Steve honors perfection in every detail. And he sees the approach of Christmas through the prism of his own pedantic gaze. He makes his family wear warm sweaters with a Christmas theme. Then he takes out an advent calendar, the days of which are painted with plans for holiday chores. In his understanding, all these attributes and symbols will instill the spirit of Christmas into the house, which will unite all family members in a special way. When new neighbors move into the house opposite, Steve is the first to rush to introduce himself as a respectable person. The newcomers are not a typical family. Buddy Hall is a loser in life. The only thing that warms the soul is a beautiful wife and two wonderful daughters. When the girls show their father a view of the area from space, Buddy is horrified to notice that their mansion is not visible. In an attempt to mark a point on the map, Buddy buys up all the holiday lights so that the lights of the garlands will become a wire beacon to the universe.',115),(6,'Once Upon a Time in Venice','The protagonist gave many years of service in the police. After going on leave, he continued to investigate cases, providing the services of a detective. And in his spare time, Steve cuts on a skateboard to keep himself in shape. When the sister\'s house is robbed by drug addicts, they take away Steve\'s dog along with the things, which has served him faithfully and faithfully for many years. For the sake of a devoted four-legged friend Buddy, Steve is ready to find and punish offenders. Yes, but he himself is not without sin. While the detective is trying to get on the trail of intruders, a real chase opens up behind him in the face of merciless bigwigs, whom Steve owes a little.',135),(7,'Clifford the Big Red Dog','A family-oriented film adaptation was released based on the stories by Norman Bridwell. Quiet and friendly Emily Elizabeth Howard lives with her mother Maggie in a tiny New York apartment. The girl is in high school and often becomes the center of ridicule among her peers. The only consolation of the heroine is communication with Owen. One day, Maggie receives an urgent work assignment to take the first flight to Chicago. The confused woman finds no other option but to leave her daughter in the care of irresponsible Uncle Casey. In the midst of the annual carnival, Emily receives an unusual red puppy as a gift from animal rescuer Mr. Bridwell. He warns the girl that the dog will grow depending on how much he gets. But how could Emily imagine that in the morning a dog of gigantic size would grow out of a small frisky puppy?! While mom is working away from home, Emily and a new friend named Clifford have unforgettable adventures ahead.',75),(8,'The Matrix Resurrections','The destroyed world becomes the dramatic finale of the long-term confrontation between people and machines. In the name of preserving sweet freedom and anticipation of triumph, people took desperate, radical steps, trying to disconnect artificial intelligence from the supply. However, extreme measures did not bring the desired result, breaking all dreams and aspirations into fragments of unfulfilled hopes. Machines have found a way that allows them to exist without artificial energy, drawing it from the human body. For the sake of this, entire farms were created, where the production of people based on a set of DNA was established. The next step of the machines was the organization of total control over people, the result of which was the creation of a matrix. However, a person who realized the whole truth of the virtual world volunteered to confront the world of technology. Neo has created resistance in the name of saving civilization, where a person rules, not a soulless mechanism. He was ready to sacrifice himself. But perhaps Neo\'s death was only the beginning of the confrontation?!',165),(9,'The Machine','The unstable situation in the world is forcing the British Ministry of Defense to seek help from professor, scientist Vincent McCarthy. An impeccable reputation, coupled with brilliant data, does not allow the leaders of the ministry to doubt the ways to solve the problem that McCarthy will offer. After a little thought, the professor finds a way out of the current situation - to create a soulless android machine. Its artificial intelligence will create an excellent platform for further development with the subsequent replacement of robots with people on the battlefield. The professor\'s proposal impresses the leadership of the kingdom - fabulous money is allocated for the creation of a trial sample. However, after creating the machine, a technical failure occurs - a minor software error causes the android to destroy the entire laboratory. The consequences of the failure radically change Vincent\'s original ideas. Now he\'s asking an AI expert to help him use the machine\'s full potential.',66);
