INSERT INTO `producers` VALUES (1,'Chloe Zhao','Zhao Ting, later known as Chloe Zhao, is an American film director, screenwriter, and producer of Chinese origin. She made the films \'Songs My Brothers Taught Me\', \'Rider\', \'Land of Nomads\'. In 2021, Zhao\'s film \'The Eternals\' was released.'),(2,'Julius Onah','Julius Onah was born on February 10, 1983 in Makurdi, Benue State, Nigeria. He is a director and producer, known for Luce (2019), Nie patrz wstecz (2008) and The Cloverfield Paradox (2018)'),(3,'Lennart Ruff','Aufgewachsen in Frankfurt a. M., Rom und Hamburg arbeitete er zun?chst f?r Werbefilmproduktionen in Hamburg und Los Angeles. Seit 2007 studiert er Spielfilmregie an der HFF M?nchen, sowie seit 2011 im Aufbaustudiengang Werbung und nahm mit seinen Kurzfilmen und Werbespots an zahlreichen Festivals teil. 2014 gewann er mit Nocebo den Studenten-Oscar f?r den besten ausl?ndischen Film (Student Academy Award in Gold, Foreign Category) der Academy of Motion Picture Arts and Sciences in Los Angeles und wurde f?r den Studio Hamburg Nachwuchspreis nominiert. 2018 wurde mit Titan ? Evolve or Die sein erster Langfilm ver?ffentlicht.'),(4,'Ari Folman','Ari Folman is an Israeli film director and screenwriter. Winner of the Golden Globe, the Cesar Award and Asia Pacific Screen Awards for the film Waltz with Bashir, the European Film Academy Award for Best Animated Film, three-time winner of the Ophir Award. Knight of the Order of Arts and Letters.'),(5,'John Whitesell','John Patrick Whitesell III is an American television and film director. He has directed numerous films such as Calendar Girl, Big Momma\'s House 2 and Vacation. He began his career as a film director in 1993.'),(6,'Mark Cullen','Mark Cullen is a screenwriter and producer. He worked as a director on some films. Most of the projects are television series in the genres of comedy, action and crime. Sometimes he works on feature films. Born in Philadelphia (Pennsylvania, USA). Has several collaborations with directors Brad Turner and Jeffrey Melman. Often works on film projects with his brother Robb Cullen, who is also a screenwriter and producer. In addition to film work, the brothers have contributed to several television shows on Fox, NBC, HBO, and Showtime. One of the first projects in the field of cinema was the television series \'Two\', which was released from 1996 to 1997. He worked on it as a screenwriter. Around the same time, he produced the series Hitz, in which he also co-wrote the script. The most successful and famous films of Mark Cullen are the Las Vegas series, the comedy Double Dick and the action comedy His Fucking Affair. In 2003, along with his brother Robb Cullen, he was nominated for an Emmy Award for writing the first episode of the comedy series Lucky. On the territory of the CIS countries, the film was not widely known.'),(7,'Walt Becker','Walter William Becker is an American film director, screenwriter, producer, and writer. Known primarily for directing the films \'King of Parties\', \'Real Boars\', \'So-So Vacation\'. Becker graduated from the USC School of Film and Television and the University of California.'),(8,'Lana Wachowski','Lana Wachowski and her sister Lilly Wachowski, also known as the Wachowskis, are the duo behind such ground-breaking movies as Matrica (1999) and Debesu ?emelapis (2012). Born to mother Lynne, a nurse, and father Ron, a businessman of Polish descent, Wachowski grew up in Chicago and formed a tight creative relationship with her sister Lilly. After the siblings dropped out of college, they started a construction business and wrote screenplays. Their 1995 script, ?udikai (1995), was made into a movie, leading to a Warner Bros contract. After that time, the Wachowskis devoted themselves to their movie careers. In 2012, during interviews for Cloud Atlas and in her acceptance speech for the Human Rights Campaign\'s Visibility Award, Lana spoke about her experience of being a transgender woman, sacrificing her much cherished anonymity out of a sense of responsibility. Lana is known to be extremely well-read, loves comic books and exploring ideas of imaginary worlds, and was inspired by Stanley Kubrick\'s 2001: Kosmin? odiseja (1968) in creating Cloud Atlas.'),(9,'Caradog W. James.','Caradog W. James is a director and producer, known for Ma?ina (2013), Little White Lies (2006) and Don\'t Knock Twice (2016).');
